===Etymology 1===
Shortened from {{term|hobby-horse}}, from {{etyl|enm}} {{term|hobyn|lang=enm}}, {{term|hobin||small horse, pony|lang=enm}}. The meaning of ''hobby-horse'' shifted from "small horse, pony" to "child's toy riding horse" to "favorite pastime or avocation" with the connecting notion being "activity that doesn't go anywhere". Possibly originally from a [[proper name]] for a horse, a diminutive of {{term|Robert}} or {{term|Robin}} (compare {{term|dobbin}}).

====Noun====
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|hobbies}}

# An activity that one enjoys doing in one's [[spare time]].
#: ''I like to collect stamps from different countries as a '''hobby'''.''
# {{context|horses}} An extinct breed of horse native to the [[British Isles]], also known as the [[w:Irish Hobby|Irish Hobby]]

